Add a plugin architecture for message format handlers and payload-compression codecs. Format handlers can be registered via the `datadog_kafka_actions.formats` entry-point group, and compression codecs via `datadog_kafka_actions.compressions`. Built-in formats (json, string, raw, bson, avro, protobuf) are now first-class plugins. New `value_compression` and `key_compression` options on the read_messages action decompress payloads before deserialization. The protobuf decode helpers `get_protobuf_message_class` and `read_protobuf_message_indices` are now public so plugin format handlers can reuse them. Additional built-in formats (`msgpack`, `protobuf_msgpack`) and compression codecs (`gzip`, `zlib`, `snappy`, `lz4`, `lz4_dd_hdr`, `zstd`) ship in this wheel; third-party codecs and the `msgpack` format require optional packages (`msgpack`, `python-snappy`, `lz4`, `zstandard`) to be installed separately.
